</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Bioware</span><hr size=1> So, where the heck is Neverwinter Nights? I've been salivating over that since it was announced way back when. I guess Interplay is out, too bad as they produced most of my favorite games of the last few years. Alas, bean counters take over and demand a profit. Corporate slimeballs. To hell with fiduciary responsibility, I want fun games! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 280<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 11:45:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=188.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bioware</span><hr size=1> Ah, I can't wait for NWN...if it is as good as alot of people predict then I will be in heaven...my EQ account may even cancel as I piece together my own world and invite some friends in for Roleplaying...won't have to put up with d00d's at all... *dreams*<br><br>Hmph...when my best friend gets out of the Corps I can totally see us setting up at least 5 dedicated servers, if not more.. <p><center><font size=+2><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bmaidensfancy">Shiden Kaidan</a></font><br>Tier'dal Knight<br><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/"> Firiona Vie</a><br><font size=1><font color=red>@}</font><font color=green>--,--'---- </font></font><br><i>"You have no power over me."</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 12:42:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=188.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bioware</span><hr size=1> Im also looking forward to NWN..... but it won't make me cancel my EQ account. <br><br>They are totally different games! <br><br>I love the massively multiplayer world aspect of EQ.... it's a lot like the real world. You run into dozens or hundreds of people every day. Some of them may be friendly, some of them may be hostile, and most of them will just ignore you and go on about their lives. <br><br>NWN won't have the same massively multiplayer feeling. It will be more like Diablo multiplayer, where you and a handful of close friends need to organize tightly planned adventures as a playing unit (e.g. a D&amp;D party), and of course one of you is the Dungeon Master Host.  <br><br>Call me crazy, but one of the reasons I play MMORPGs in the first place (like Everquest) is for the chance to encounter new people, new acquaintances, and to explore new worlds and regions.... rather than to play with people and real life friends I already know (most of them wont play games anyways). It's that sense of unfamiliarity that I like. <br><br>In NeverwinterNights, as a player character you likely will know that your Dungeon Master Host is your older cousin Bob or your best friend Jason who runs a T1 server from his apartment, who you can probably bribe him off some $10 to give you a +5 paladin sword.... <br><br>For some people, this kind of familiarity is a blessing.... knowing that you know everyone who is in your party, and in some cases you may even end up being a personal real life friend of your DMs.  That's perfectly fine..... but definitely a much different type of multiplayer environment from MMORPGs like EQ or DAoC. <br><br>I will try out NWN when it comes out..... but at the moment, the only game that currently stands a chance of directly competing with EQ (and stealing my attention) is Verant's own upcoming Star Wars Galaxies MMORPG. But that's still a looooong ways away, they are promising a gigantic project yet they don't even seem to be ready to start beta testing yet.  <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 285<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/24/02 2:30:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=188.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Bioware</span><hr size=1> Bah...that's a limited scope of things.  Play in a private UO shard...you'll see much better people in some of them then you would playing Origin's shards.  And yes, you can just meet people you don't know.  Ever play Vampire: The Masquerade - Redemption?  I've played in and ran dozens of games, all with people I do not know, and all without being MMORPG.<br><br>When Baldur's Gate first came out, I played with a bunch of people that I only knew as posters to a newsgroup, and like 91% of those people were in the UK.  Much like here on FV I didn't know them other than their online personas.<br><br>Personally, I like having the power to kickban someone if they are being an @$$, something I can't do in EQ. <p><center><font size=+2><a href="http://pub66.ezboard.com/bmaidensfancy">Shiden Kaidan</a></font><br>Tier'dal Knight<br><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/"> Firiona Vie</a><br><font size=1><font color=red>@}</font><font color=green>--,--'---- </font></font><br><i>"You have no power over me."</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.c